<p>The <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="thinkreshapeButton.msg+thinkreshapeButton+50">Mesh Boundaries</span> command enables you to extract the bounds of a mesh in form of polyline (NURBS with degree 1) that are created at the boundaries.</p>

<ol class="noleft">
<li>Select the mesh whose boundaries you want to extract.<br>
<br>
To reset the mesh selection, right-click on <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="thinkreshapePlugin.msg+_ThinkReshape_LABEL_+3">Mesh</span> in the selection list, choose the <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="tdesign.msg+_INTEL_LABEL_+33">Reset</span> option in the context menu and then select the mesh again.<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>All the existing boundaries get highlighted. You can select those boundaries that are to be extracted.<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>If you select the <span class="UI_OPTION" id="thinkreshapePlugin.msg+_ThinkReshape_LABEL_+158">Select All</span> check box, all the highlighted boundaries will get extracted.<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>Click the <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="GUIService.msg+_GUISERVICE_TOOLTIP_+1">OK</span> button <img src="../../../images/general/OKbutton.gif" align="absmiddle"> to confirm the operation, or the <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="GUIService.msg+_GUISERVICE_TOOLTIP_+2">Cancel</span> button <img src="../../../images/general/CANCELbutton.gif" align="absmiddle"> to abort.<br>
<br>
